    "dfiaplattfM Xjt Earner M 7hree QVorJs By Chaplain Charles F OGorman Many writers who have a way with words also have because they are masters of their craft a manner of using very few and saying so very much with them It is quite likely that skilled authors could express all the feelings in the world by using simple threeword phrases The mightiest truth of them all could well be expressed in this manner No one set of words could surpass God Loves You The more human aspect of the same feeling has been adequately described in song and verse by the wellknown words I Love You Statesmen have made great decisions poets have gained fame with the lyrics song writers have wooed the world They used only these oftrepeated three little words Amid all the combinations that have ever been used there is one phra23 that expresses more un told emotions than any other set of three This trio can be the out let of a number of feelings that belong to the human heart It would take many pages and many examples to cover them all Take the man who has failed at something for which he worked"
